==Postseason== Quarterback [[Joe Flacco]] was invited to participate in the 2008 [[NFL Scouting Combine]] that took place February 21â24, 2008.<ref>{{cite news |title=University of Delaware Football Standout Joe Flacco to Take Part in NFL Combine This Week; Highlights on NFL Network and nfl.com |url=http://www.bluehens.com/sportsinfo/football/fb07-flacconflcombine.html |work=University of Delaware |date=February 20, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-19}}</ref> Flacco was selected to play in the 83rd [[East-West Shrine Game]] that took place on January 19, 2008 at the [[University of Houston]]'s [[Robertson Stadium]],<ref>{{cite news |title=University of Delaware Quarterback Joe Flacco to Participate in East-West Shrine All-Star Game Jan. 19 in Houston |url=http://www.bluehens.com/sportsinfo/football/fb07-flaccoshrine.html |work=University of Delaware |date=January 7, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-19}}</ref> but declined after he was invited to play in the [[2008 Senior Bowl]] that took place on January 26, 2008 at [[Ladd-Peebles Stadium]] in [[Mobile, Alabama]].<ref>{{cite news |title=University of Delaware Quarterback Joe Flacco Forgoes Shrine Game to Play in Under Armour Senior Bowl |url=http://www.bluehens.com/sportsinfo/football/fb07-flaccosenior.html |work=University of Delaware |date=January 15, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-19}}</ref>
Flacco was selected by the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in the first round (18th overall) of the [[2008 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Powell, Camille |title=Ravens Deal to Land Delaware QB Flacco |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/04/26/AR2008042601724.html |work=[[Washington Post]] |date=April 27, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-23}}</ref> Flacco was the only Blue Hen selected in the draft, but three other players signed with NFL teams as [[undrafted free agent]]s. Offensive guard Rich Beverley was signed by the [[Washington Redskins]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Delawareâs Beverley signs with Washington |url=http://www.udel.edu/PR/UDaily/2008/may/beverley050508.html |work=University of Delaware |date=May 5, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-23}}</ref> offensive tackle [[Mike Byrne (American football)|Mike Byrne]] was signed by the [[Miami Dolphins]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Cuff signs with Titans, Byrne with Dolphins |url=http://www.udel.edu/PR/UDaily/2008/apr/nfl042908.html |work=University of Delaware |date=April 29, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-23}}</ref> and running back [[Omar Cuff]] was signed by the [[Tennessee Titans]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Hens' Cuff, Byrne accept free-agent deals |url=http://www.delawareonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080428/SPORTS07/804280357/1002/SPORTS |work=delawareonline.com |date=April 28, 2008 |accessdate=2010-07-23}}</ref>
